A second youth has died in as many days in Buffalo City Metro after coming into contact with exposed live electrical wires. Michael-John Meyer, 14, from Parkridge, was electrocuted in front of his home on Saturday evening, just a day after a young King William s Town boy died in a similar fashion.A day before Michael-John was killed, Grade 1 Dale College pupil Tinashe Luminathi Siwisa from King William s Town was electrocuted when he came into contact with an unlocked electricity transformer outside his West Bank home.The boy was declared dead on arrival at a local doctor s surgery.For the full story get a copy of the Dispatch or subscribe to our e-Edition for the complete newspaper with jobs, classifieds, crosswords, TV schedules and back editions &nbsp;